Text.string: Damn... it's not working.
Something's wrong. I should be able to charge it. We need help.
Are you Tannis?
Tannis, I presume.
You must be Tannis.
You Tannis?
We can't let them get the map!
Defend the map!
Keep fighting, Vault Hunter!
(fall react)
Just park the rig right there, VH.
(catch effort)
One sec, I'll get to fueling.
She's fueled!
Oh! Oh! Ohhh! Oh-hohh, hoo!
Hurry, Vault Hunter! Ain't no one touchin' our ship, and Lil needs help!
Get down there, VH! Lil needs us!
I... I'll be all right. Let's get to the ship.
(map catch effort)
Park that fine ass of yours in the driver's seat, hon.
VH. You do know how to drive, right?
Give that rig a ride!
Well, get in, sweet stuff.
See? Turns 'em right into bio-fuel. I'm trying to expand the Catch-A-Ride franchise and corner the sustainable fuel business.
I know it's messy, but the only resource Pandora's got in abundance anymore are bandits and skags. Use what the land gives ya, right?
Halfway there, Vault Hunter! We'll have that spaceship fueled in no time!
While I examine this unimaginably complex and priceless alien artifact, you may wait outside and steal anything not nailed down.
Let's top her off. Just a little more bio-fuel.
Kill those damn bandits!
Kill 'em all!
Wipe 'em out, VH!
Take out them cultist sumbitches!
VH! Get on the damn ship, hon!
Get on the ship!
Come on, we got to go!
What're ya waiting for? Ship's ready to take off!
Vault Hunter... help... me...
I am. You must be Lilith's new Vault Hunter. And you've found the map! I suppose congratulations are in order.||That was it. Well? Let me take a look.
Runs in the family.
Let's give this Firehawk thing a try! Where are my Eridium-tier followers at? Hah! Loving it!
Don't forget to like, follow, and obey!
All right! Let's get out of here. I wanna see if Katagawa's good on his word. Leave the scraps to the dogs.
And your powers! I'll make sure to finish what you started.
Firehawk. Just give me the map.
I need to use you as a sounding board for my hypotheses. Please do not confuse it for conversation.
No. Way.
Cool. Let's DO THIS!
Ach—got it!
Ohoohoohoo, this is gold!
What are you... doing?!
Well, I've taken your powers—might as well finish you off.
Whew! Thanks for the lift, Lil. It's finally happenin', ain't it? After all these years.
Hell yeah. How's the ship looking?
I'll start rounding up the Raiders and bring them on-board.
The Vaults hold unimaginable power, you know. But I shudder to think of what might happen if the Calypso Twins reach them first.
It's an ambush! Rrgh, damn door's busted! Take the lift to the catwalk—I'll try to get the door open.
Ooooh! Uh-uh-uh.
Help her up, VH! We got to get Lil to the ship.
I didn't think I'd ever see this thing again. It's not just a map, though. We used this to open the other Vaults on Pandora. Every Vault needs its Key.
It's not charged. Let me take care of that.
I'll catch up when I can. Have to track down a few loose ends for our ship.
Hrgh—YAGHHHH!
As I suspected, Tyreen Calypso is a Siren. She seems to feed on the lifeforce of others. And clearly her cult is her food source, for now.
(bloodthirsty screaming)
I did what I could, Lilith, given my vast intellect but limited resources. Shall we give it a go?
Lilith! If you're listening, bandits are attacking my dig site, and it's not the sort of breakthrough I was hoping for!
Tannis, are you okay?
No, but you're all still here in my personal space, so let's get on with it.
And I believe this should do it...
Oh, you know I abhor this, Lilith.
Just trying to keep my Eridian expert safe.
Do you know ANOTHER Eridian expert?
Ready?
All right. Later, Lil.
Now, if that rig gets a Pandora flat and busts out into holy hellfire, just come on back and I'll set ya up with another, sweet thang.

Hmm... some data has been corrupted. It seems the map has sustained significant damage. Hypothesis! Tyreen Calypso attempted to charge the map, but her powers only drained it further. Unfortunately, I can only make out a single planet.
Like I said, you just need to run over some bandits and skags and whatnot.
Astronav chip should be nearby. We ain't gonna get all the way to Promethea without one.
Yo Ellie, got that astronav chip!
I found that astronav chip, Ellie.
Ellie, I have acquired the astronav chip.
Got that astronav, Ellie.
Now come on back, and I'll get to refueling.
Just gotta few more things to—what the hell is that?!
Vault Hunter, over here.
Ugh! This is bad, but now ain't the time to talk it through, amigo! We gotta get the hell out of here. And that ship is the safest place I know.
Damn, more COV! Kill 'em quick, Vault Hunter. We got to get the hell out of here!
(pain reactions)
Promethea? Of course! Typhon DeLeon found the very first Vault there, you know.
Look what those bastards did to Lil! Kill 'em, VH!
Vault... Hunter...
Do you hear screaming, or am I having another one of my episodes?
Could be both, but we definitely have company. Incoming!
Uh huh! I'll introduce them to my fists.
It's not just you. There's blood on the wind.
Maybe? I always hear screaming.
Heya superfan, you fix the map yet? Just hand it over, and you can join our family—but wait, what's that? You don't want to? K, gave you a chance, real bummer.
So long, Crimson Traitors!
Troy's gon—heh, “Crimson Traitors”, nice. Anyway, my brother's gonna broadcast your death on the ECHOnet!
So don't, you know, say anything stupidly heroic. I'll just dub over it.
I'm on my way. Vault Hunter, don't let them anywhere near Tannis or that map.
All right, killer. Let's take the rest out together.
I'll hold onto the astronav chip for now, hon.
Tell me you got the map working.
There's only one person on this planet who knows how this Eridian tech works. Patricia Tannis. She's got a dig site on the other side of the valley. Take the map to her.
You hold onto that astronav chip for now, hon.
Promethea... Good work, Tannis.
Looks like it. We have to get to that Vault before the Calypsos. Ellie's been working on a ship for us. I'll take Tannis and the map there now. Meet you at the landing pad, Vault Hunter.
Be ready for anything, Ellie. The Calypsos aren't gonna let us leave without a fight.
It's time! Ooh, I can't wait to leave Pandora! I've been here so long it's in my bones, and that's a verified medical condition anywhere else ya go.
I got somethin' special for ya, VH!
Ready to go, killer?
What the hell?!
So... destination Promethea?
Promethea-bound, are we?
Our destination is Promethea, then?
We're off to Promethea, then?

Usually when I step in crap, it comes off with a good wipe, but you? You're kind of a clinger. Let me set things straight for you. That map, and every Vault on it, is my birthright. You don't understand a thing about the Vaults, or what they're even for. I do. We're the Children of the Vault. It's a family thing.

Hey, superfan! You sure you picked the right team? I mean, I get it. We all grew up wanting to be Vault Hunters. But I'm not a follower like you. I'm a god. And my followers will do anything I ask. Ooh, here, quick demo.||—Hey, you! Cut off your favorite leg.
Almost ready. All I need is some fuel and a new astronav chip.
On it.
Of course I can.
Of course.
Sure, why not?
That vehicle over there's my biofuel rig. And it ain't picky as to the source. Just run over some bandits and skags to fill her up. Environmentally friendly, right? Hop on in, Vault Hunter.
Now we just need an astronav chip. It's essential for space navigation and such. There's one in some old Dahl wreckage you can plunder.
I've almost got the whole crew on-board. As soon as you get that astronav chip, we're taking off.
And I knew you would, Vault Hunter! Come on back now. Time to get the hell of this forsaken wasteland I call home. Next stop, Promethea!
I can't believe we're going to Promethea! It'll be good to see some new sights and lay some new lays. Gonna teach them city boys some things they only see in nature documentaries!
I'm headed to the ship. See you soon, killer.

I'm gettin' this vibe that you don't really get what we're doing here. Let me learn ya real quick—see, my brother and I were born into a cage. Dad told us it was for our own good, that the rest of the universe was full of bandits that would tear us apart. And when we finally got free, it turned out he was right. Bandits as far as the eye could see.

Hustle up, everybody! Get on the ship! You heard the Commander! Scrub those decks, batten down the interns! We're leavin' this parched armpit behind, the stars our destination! Screw you, Pandora! You can't hurt us anymore!
Vault... Hunter...

Bandits were the biggest untapped resource in the galaxy! There are billions of them across the borderlands, human wreckage left over from the corporate wars. They're broken, but we make them feel special, so they fight for us. And die for us. Because they finally have a place where they belong. A family. My family. The universe is theirs... as long as they obey.
At least you got the map.
Well, let's take a look. Been a long time.
You're a Siren?
Heh. Yeah... well...
Vault Hunter—can you help Ellie get the ship prepped?
I'm the Siren. He's just a parasite. Literally. When we were born, our father had to cut him off me! Now I'M the only thing keeping him alive.
I can leech the power from any living thing. Even you, Firehawk.
Legendary Vault Hunter. Slayer of the Destroyer. Firehawk. So many titles, so little impact!
Ngh... Ty... Tyreen!
For Tyreen! GHRAAAAAAGH!
Fine.
Damn, we kicked your ass! What now, Liarhawk?
Man, you should've seen your face. You, you, you were like, “Oh, my powers! Boo-hoo!”
(fight react)
Smile!
Ty—Ty, c'mon! We're live in three, two...
What is up, brothers and sisters? God-Queen Tyreen coming to ya live. We got something real special for ya today. Your number one, most-requested murder! It's the Great Heretic herself: the Firehawk!
(face-off)
Well, look who got plucked!
But that's not all! Our path to the Great Vault has been revealed. Next stop: Promethea!
Freakin' crushed it! Ooh, one sec. Get in, Ty.
Freakin' crushed it! Ooh, whaddya say we document the occasion?
I knew them COV sumbitches wouldn't let us leave Pandora without a fight. Well, they're gon' get it!
Don't feel bad, Lil. All legends have to die. You had a good run.||—I guess? That's just something people say. I don't really believe it.
(face-off)
Later, Firehawk! Or whatever you are now.
Buh-bye, now. Thanks for the map!
(fight effort)
Help her up, Vault Hunter!
Man, the rakks really hit the turbine!
Get her to her feet. We gotta go before those cult bastards come back to finish her off!
This ain't good! What'd they do to her?
I've got you—on your feet, Commander.
You'll be okay, sister.
Commander, we should go.
You're all right. Come on.
Thanks, Vault Hunter.
VH! Get on the ship! We gotta get outta here before more of them COV sumbitches attack!
(push reaction)
Vault Hunter... I can't...
(slap react)
(backhand)
(fight charge-up)
(blown across the room)
(camera stomp)
(punch Troy)
(punch react)
(breathing hard)
(choke react)
(choke react continued)
Hello, person trampling my valuable and irreplaceable dig site. May I help you?
(pain react)
(annoyed throw)
(landing react)
(crawling efforts)
(kick effort)
(kick react)
(push effort)
I didn't say bo—he cut off both. Ugh, now he's trying to stand on his stumps. One sec.

Mmmmm. They just taste better when they're afraid. What was my point? Oh! Right. My followers will die for me. And when it's your turn, I'll let you know. Now run along, superfan. Fix that map for me. Those Vaults are mine.
COV, incoming!
